{"TopicId":158024,"ForumId":15,"TopicTitle":"How to make textures","CreatedByName":"Benjamin Kerman","CreatedById":172792,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T17:19:57Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Benjamin Kerman","CreatedById":172792,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T17:19:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe title says it all. I am using blender, any suggestions?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SchwinnTropius","CreatedById":165170,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T18:09:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere may be a feature in Blender to paint directly on your UV layout, but I haven\u0027t figured out how to use it. I export the UV layout to .png and use an image editor to make the texture.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, it seems you posted this multiple times, may want to have a moderator address the duplicates.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-21T18:10:26Z\u0022 title=\u002203/21/2017 06:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 21, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by SchwinnTropius\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"martinezfg11","CreatedById":59995,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T18:12:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/L7ALfRw6I5I?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/LcCQKuWPhXk?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mad Rocket Scientist","CreatedById":139256,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-21T23:40:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA couple of good KSP tutorials:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/85134-intermediate-texturing-guide-colour-specular-and-normal-maps/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/87505-intermediate-texturing-panels-and-edge-damage/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA big thread with lots of hints:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/127093-texturing-uv-mapping-megathread-share-your-techniques-and-tricks/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMake sure to read this one, advice from Porkjet on how the stock textures are made:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/114738-need-advice-on-not-making-colors-seem-quotflatquot/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2037490\u0026amp;embedComment=2037490\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-2037490\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAmbient occlusion and normal maps will make your textures look much better for very little work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKeep everything in a separate layer for easier workflow.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}